SIMPLE: mortally
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mortally
<hw>Mor"tal*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a mortal
manner; so as to cause death; <as>as, <ex>mortally</ex>
wounded</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In the manner of a mortal or of mortal
beings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I was <qex>mortally</qex> brought forth.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In an extreme degree; to the point of dying or
causing death; desperately; <as>as, <ex>mortally</ex>
jealous</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Adrian <qex>mortally</qex> envied poets, painters, and artificers,
in works wherein he had a vein to excel.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mortalness</ent>⟦br⟧
